1
00:01:26,770 --> 00:01:30,770
=My Dear Guardian=

2
00:01:31,340 --> 00:01:34,120
=Episode 16=

3
00:01:36,077 --> 00:01:37,517
Madam suddenly fainted this morning.

4
00:01:37,558 --> 00:01:39,219
Teacher insists to hurry back to Dong'an.

5
00:01:39,260 --> 00:01:41,019
I had no choice but to call you.

6
00:01:41,060 --> 00:01:42,990
Tang Lin, is the car ready?

7
00:01:43,386 --> 00:01:44,426
Professor Xia.

8
00:01:45,130 --> 00:01:46,165
-It's ready.
-Let's get going.

9
00:01:46,206 --> 00:01:47,480
Yes, right away.

10
00:01:48,232 --> 00:01:50,160
Professor Xia,
are you going back to Dong'an tonight?

11
00:01:50,201 --> 00:01:51,400
It's a family emergency.

12
00:01:51,873 --> 00:01:52,773
What are you waiting for?

13
00:01:53,465 --> 00:01:54,646
Professor Xia, don't worry.

14
00:01:54,687 --> 00:01:56,920
I have a way to get you home
quicker and safer.

15
00:01:57,745 --> 00:01:58,895
Get me home quicker?

16
00:01:59,096 --> 00:02:00,046
Leave it to me.

17
00:02:21,383 --> 00:02:23,532
Which do you like to eat,
cherries or grapes?

18
00:03:08,624 --> 00:03:10,680
Liang Shao Xue, what are you doing?

19
00:03:10,721 --> 00:03:13,771
This is my latest original composition!

20
00:03:16,272 --> 00:03:18,280
It's to commemorate my okay!

21
00:03:18,707 --> 00:03:21,614
-I can't find him anymore!
-Give it to me.

22
00:03:21,655 --> 00:03:24,560
I'll immortalize him in my song!

23
00:03:29,896 --> 00:03:31,116
Liang Shao Xue,

24
00:03:31,485 --> 00:03:33,919
are you still having jet lag
or did you leave your brain...

25
00:03:33,959 --> 00:03:35,973
behind at the other side of the Pacific?

26
00:03:36,314 --> 00:03:37,159
Believe it or not,

27
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:38,510
with your unearthly screech,

28
00:03:38,551 --> 00:03:41,098
Okay will not be okay
even if he heard you.

29
00:03:41,139 --> 00:03:42,720
Of course I don't believe it!

30
00:03:42,761 --> 00:03:43,984
What's wrong with this tone?

31
00:03:44,025 --> 00:03:45,680
My brother likes it so much.

32
00:03:45,721 --> 00:03:47,200
I even made him an album.

33
00:03:47,241 --> 00:03:49,560
He listens to it in the car everyday!

34
00:03:51,227 --> 00:03:53,522
Play a song.
Whose songs are your favourite?

35
00:03:53,563 --> 00:03:54,813
Mandarin or English?

36
00:04:01,588 --> 00:04:02,455
This...

37
00:04:02,877 --> 00:04:04,157
Who sang this?

38
00:04:04,198 --> 00:04:05,778
You have some heavy tastes.

39
00:04:11,021 --> 00:04:12,800
So it was you.

40
00:04:28,823 --> 00:04:29,960
Liang Shao Xue!

41
00:04:31,057 --> 00:04:32,397
I can't do this anymore.

42
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:48,440
Answer the phone, Liang Mu Ze!

43
00:05:13,023 --> 00:05:15,120
I was busy, what's wrong?

44
00:05:16,073 --> 00:05:17,640
Why is it so noisy?

45
00:05:19,385 --> 00:05:20,360
Hang on!

46
00:05:25,313 --> 00:05:27,112
Liang Mu Ze, what are you doing?

47
00:05:27,153 --> 00:05:28,760
Why did you tell Xue that...

48
00:05:42,854 --> 00:05:43,804
Xia Chu,

49
00:05:45,447 --> 00:05:46,517
what's wrong with Xue?

50
00:05:49,007 --> 00:05:50,387
Nothing.

51
00:05:51,191 --> 00:05:53,211
It's just the music she plays...

52
00:05:53,252 --> 00:05:54,165
I understand.

53
00:05:54,953 --> 00:05:57,283
I'll call her later.

54
00:05:58,064 --> 00:05:59,160
Anything else?

55
00:05:59,633 --> 00:06:01,040
The...

56
00:06:02,147 --> 00:06:06,040
Did you put the cherries
on the balcony?

57
00:06:06,903 --> 00:06:07,800
Yes.

58
00:06:08,297 --> 00:06:11,833
I went to visit Xiao Jun and stopped by.

59
00:06:12,643 --> 00:06:13,680
Are they doing well?

60
00:06:14,021 --> 00:06:14,872
They're great.

61
00:06:14,913 --> 00:06:16,863
They'll be at the unit on New Year's Day.

62
00:06:16,953 --> 00:06:18,080
I'll go too.

63
00:06:19,346 --> 00:06:21,236
Our hospital organized a medical team...

64
00:06:21,277 --> 00:06:22,657
to provide medical
examination for you guys.

65
00:06:24,243 --> 00:06:25,223
Okay, then.

66
00:06:25,619 --> 00:06:27,009
I'll see you there.

67
00:06:27,442 --> 00:06:28,322
Okay.

68
00:06:28,961 --> 00:06:35,531
♪I am afraid that
I might lose you one day♪

69
00:06:35,982 --> 00:06:42,502
♪Every minute, every second,
how do I resist?♪

70
00:06:43,086 --> 00:06:49,686
♪I can't help but look forward
to your return♪

71
00:06:50,139 --> 00:06:56,840
♪To relive the moment
my heart skipped a beat♪

72
00:07:27,945 --> 00:07:34,880
♪Romance makes little things feel warm♪

73
00:07:37,538 --> 00:07:44,329
♪Warmth softens even a stubborn heart♪

74
00:07:47,202 --> 00:07:50,692
♪Heart is filled
with your little company everyday♪

75
00:07:50,733 --> 00:07:51,800
I'll give you one.

76
00:07:57,145 --> 00:08:04,119
♪Can't miss a thing about you,
hence there is no regrets♪

77
00:08:06,773 --> 00:08:07,873
What are you looking at?

78
00:08:08,391 --> 00:08:09,360
Does it smell nice?

79
00:08:11,743 --> 00:08:15,013
♪Spending every minute to stay with you♪

80
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:21,432
♪Liking what you like,
sensitive to every detail♪

81
00:08:21,473 --> 00:08:24,973
♪My heart is at peace closer to you♪

82
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:30,922
♪Liking your habits,
remembering small moments♪

83
00:08:30,963 --> 00:08:32,320
Do you want to eat it?

84
00:08:35,941 --> 00:08:40,904
♪Liking what you like,
sensitive to every detail♪

85
00:08:40,945 --> 00:08:44,465
♪My heart is at peace closer to you♪

86
00:08:45,660 --> 00:08:48,481
♪Liking your habits,
remembering small moments♪

87
00:08:48,522 --> 00:08:50,620
When a girl is of age,
she must be married off.

88
00:08:50,661 --> 00:08:52,471
Stay still, Er Miao.

89
00:08:53,659 --> 00:08:54,720
How naughty you are!

90
00:08:55,525 --> 00:09:00,343
♪Getting used to what you like,
trying to be brave♪

91
00:09:00,384 --> 00:09:06,354
♪Liking becomes natural
and turns into a habit♪

92
00:09:14,333 --> 00:09:15,320
Xia.

93
00:09:16,273 --> 00:09:17,293
Lie down.

94
00:09:18,043 --> 00:09:18,960
How do you feel?

95
00:09:19,365 --> 00:09:20,305
I'm fine.

96
00:09:20,657 --> 00:09:21,827
It's old weakness.

97
00:09:22,703 --> 00:09:24,643
Luckily, I have Yue Hua
to keep me company.

98
00:09:28,152 --> 00:09:30,492
-Thank you.
-You're welcome, Professor Xia.

99
00:09:30,533 --> 00:09:32,326
We've been neighbours for years.

100
00:09:32,367 --> 00:09:35,483
I was thinking to accompany her
for the night if you didn't come back.

101
00:09:35,643 --> 00:09:36,733
How could I not come back?

102
00:09:36,774 --> 00:09:38,320
I'll come back for sure.

103
00:09:38,533 --> 00:09:39,813
Then you accompany Zi Yu.

104
00:09:39,854 --> 00:09:40,840
I'll leave first.

105
00:09:41,313 --> 00:09:42,533
Okay, goodbye.

106
00:09:42,574 --> 00:09:43,494
Thank you, Yue Hua.

107
00:09:43,535 --> 00:09:44,800
Take care, goodbye.

108
00:09:50,593 --> 00:09:52,280
Madam, how do you feel?

109
00:09:54,063 --> 00:09:55,040
Aunty.

110
00:09:59,178 --> 00:10:01,518
Didn't you say there's
no flight ticket left?

111
00:10:02,573 --> 00:10:03,760
How did you get back?

112
00:10:06,553 --> 00:10:07,840
We didn't get to buy the tickets.

113
00:10:08,309 --> 00:10:11,680
He sent me back with his company's
private plane.

114
00:10:15,562 --> 00:10:17,112
Sorry to trouble you.

115
00:10:17,153 --> 00:10:19,413
It's nothing as long as you're fine.

116
00:10:20,883 --> 00:10:24,063
Zhuo Ran, let's have a seat and rest.

117
00:10:24,613 --> 00:10:26,523
You've worked hard along the way.

118
00:10:26,736 --> 00:10:28,560
It's fine, I have to rush back.

119
00:10:28,601 --> 00:10:29,640
I have meeting tomorrow morning.

120
00:10:29,998 --> 00:10:32,301
I'll come and visit you
after getting this done.

121
00:10:32,342 --> 00:10:33,242
Get some rest.

122
00:10:34,349 --> 00:10:35,229
Okay.

123
00:10:35,443 --> 00:10:36,723
Tang Lin, send him off for me.

124
00:10:36,764 --> 00:10:38,000
Send him off.

125
00:10:38,423 --> 00:10:39,920
-Aunt, goodbye.
-Goodbye.

126
00:10:50,363 --> 00:10:53,640
Mr. Zhuo, we must still be
on our way if it wasn't you.

127
00:10:54,103 --> 00:10:55,160
Thank you.

128
00:10:55,813 --> 00:10:57,443
Xia Chu is my former classmate.

129
00:10:57,484 --> 00:10:59,892
It's the least I can do.

130
00:10:59,933 --> 00:11:00,953
I think...

131
00:11:00,994 --> 00:11:04,174
it's more than just a former classmate.

132
00:11:05,663 --> 00:11:07,733
Teacher even asked
me how I feel about you.

133
00:11:07,809 --> 00:11:10,780
I answered him right away
that you're a young talent.

134
00:11:10,821 --> 00:11:12,231
-I'm flattered.
-It's true.

135
00:11:12,473 --> 00:11:13,903
If I've got what you have,

136
00:11:13,944 --> 00:11:15,232
I'll go to the United States
by my private plane...

137
00:11:15,273 --> 00:11:17,080
and propose to my girlfriend right away.

138
00:11:17,301 --> 00:11:19,481
But your strategy is correct too.

139
00:11:19,633 --> 00:11:20,840
Get the hardest part done first.

140
00:11:21,753 --> 00:11:22,903
Your girlfriend is in the United State?

141
00:11:22,944 --> 00:11:23,794
Yes.

142
00:11:24,422 --> 00:11:26,109
We've been in a long-distance
relationship for years.

143
00:11:26,150 --> 00:11:27,800
I wonder how long it can last.

144
00:11:31,793 --> 00:11:32,760
Are you Mr. Zhuo?

145
00:11:33,773 --> 00:11:34,680
This is my ride.

146
00:11:35,073 --> 00:11:36,070
I'll drop you off first.

147
00:11:36,922 --> 00:11:37,992
Never mind, it's not convenient.

148
00:11:38,033 --> 00:11:39,360
-Let's go together.
-No.

149
00:11:39,723 --> 00:11:41,463
-You sit here.
-Okay.

150
00:11:48,433 --> 00:11:49,333
Xia,

151
00:11:50,307 --> 00:11:53,293
is the private plane huge?

152
00:11:53,383 --> 00:11:54,760
How is it like on the inside?

153
00:11:56,316 --> 00:11:57,856
I didn't pay attention to it.

154
00:11:58,813 --> 00:12:00,393
All I thought about was you.

155
00:12:06,263 --> 00:12:07,680
Look at you.

156
00:12:09,063 --> 00:12:11,122
You were the one who kicked him out.

157
00:12:11,163 --> 00:12:13,143
And now you're the one
who got on his plane.

158
00:12:13,698 --> 00:12:15,308
I don't know what's on your mind.

159
00:12:15,663 --> 00:12:17,230
What do you mean?

160
00:12:17,271 --> 00:12:18,160
Don't play dumb.

161
00:12:18,782 --> 00:12:21,800
Do you think he's here to
send an old man like you back?

162
00:12:24,655 --> 00:12:29,209
Things like private planes and
private yachts...

163
00:12:29,250 --> 00:12:32,150
can only appear in a soap opera.

164
00:12:32,890 --> 00:12:34,550
He's here for your daughter.

165
00:12:36,203 --> 00:12:39,398
I'm fine with that if he can really
handle that girl.

166
00:12:41,115 --> 00:12:42,255
You don't oppose them?

167
00:12:43,583 --> 00:12:44,720
Why would I oppose them?

168
00:12:45,783 --> 00:12:47,979
Didn't he break your daughter's heart?

169
00:12:48,743 --> 00:12:50,920
Didn't you always complain that
I broke your heart?

170
00:12:57,276 --> 00:13:00,096
They were just chipping away
when they were at school.

171
00:13:01,809 --> 00:13:03,285
People will grow up,

172
00:13:03,326 --> 00:13:04,480
especially a man.

173
00:13:04,975 --> 00:13:07,035
The point is how they get along.

174
00:13:07,971 --> 00:13:09,192
Anyway,

175
00:13:09,233 --> 00:13:11,400
as long as it's not the soldier guy.

176
00:13:11,441 --> 00:13:12,440
Who is that soldier guy?

177
00:13:15,153 --> 00:13:16,963
You don't have to worry.

178
00:13:17,100 --> 00:13:18,023
Get some sleep.

179
00:13:18,064 --> 00:13:19,960
No, who is that soldier guy?

180
00:13:22,822 --> 00:13:24,052
I'll go and do some research.

181
00:13:24,093 --> 00:13:25,080
Get some sleep.

182
00:13:34,914 --> 00:13:36,200
Did he mean that guy?

183
00:13:37,887 --> 00:13:40,187
The scientific name of parrot
is Blue-eyed Cockatoo.

184
00:13:40,439 --> 00:13:42,499
Its common name is
Sulphur-crested Cockatoo.

185
00:13:42,933 --> 00:13:44,640
And it's called
Australian White Chicken too.

186
00:13:44,681 --> 00:13:49,482
It's a rare species
but it has average language skills.

187
00:13:53,279 --> 00:13:54,840
It even speaks English!

188
00:13:54,881 --> 00:13:56,520
Seems like its gene is mutated.

189
00:13:58,454 --> 00:14:00,480
Do you know
what the mark on its foot means?

190
00:14:02,005 --> 00:14:03,840
It probably belongs to an institution.

191
00:14:04,135 --> 00:14:05,662
I don't know the exact situation too.

192
00:14:05,703 --> 00:14:07,360
I have to look it up.

193
00:14:09,463 --> 00:14:11,400
Then what are you going to do with it?

194
00:14:12,263 --> 00:14:13,452
According to the procedure,

195
00:14:13,493 --> 00:14:15,193
it would be great if we could
find its original institution.

196
00:14:15,413 --> 00:14:16,757
If not,

197
00:14:16,798 --> 00:14:18,378
we'll just find a new institution.

198
00:14:18,836 --> 00:14:22,532
But
this little thing is quite fierce...

199
00:14:22,573 --> 00:14:24,720
based on my contact with it just now.

200
00:14:25,677 --> 00:14:27,760
I didn't succeed in my repeated trials.

201
00:14:28,423 --> 00:14:31,320
Seems like that will cause problems
if we forcibly take it away.

202
00:14:34,423 --> 00:14:37,283
I feel that
you're getting along with it.

203
00:14:37,623 --> 00:14:38,763
Why don't...

204
00:14:40,277 --> 00:14:41,680
you take care of it for a few days?

205
00:14:42,808 --> 00:14:46,233
I'll take it back after I find its owner.

206
00:14:46,575 --> 00:14:47,462
No problem.

207
00:14:47,503 --> 00:14:50,283
But can it work
as I don't have the related documents?

208
00:14:51,376 --> 00:14:52,876
It's just temporary.

209
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:54,900
Look at this little guy,

210
00:14:55,183 --> 00:14:56,932
it's energetic and strong.

211
00:14:56,973 --> 00:14:58,740
It might have almost recovered.

212
00:14:59,215 --> 00:15:02,132
I'll send you some
matters needing attention when I go back.

213
00:15:02,173 --> 00:15:03,360
You just need to follow them.

214
00:15:03,401 --> 00:15:06,400
Like the environment,
the food you feed it...

215
00:15:06,441 --> 00:15:08,311
and the water supply and so on.

216
00:15:08,653 --> 00:15:09,843
Just don't let it fly away.

217
00:15:10,730 --> 00:15:11,573
Okay.

218
00:15:11,614 --> 00:15:12,594
Sorry to bother you.

219
00:15:13,431 --> 00:15:14,921
I'm counting on you.

220
00:15:28,264 --> 00:15:31,044
Toleration song sings
of numerous tolerances.

221
00:15:32,206 --> 00:15:34,026
Being tolerant is the decency
of a great man.

222
00:15:35,173 --> 00:15:36,683
Being tolerant is the root of a gentleman.

223
00:15:38,023 --> 00:15:39,762
He could endure the heat of the summer.

224
00:15:39,803 --> 00:15:41,320
He could endure the cold of the winter.

225
00:15:42,893 --> 00:15:44,623
He could be happy
while enduring the poverty.

226
00:15:45,533 --> 00:15:48,108
He could be eternal by enduring life.

